ANNOTATION
Research Objective: The development of the RuhVR virtual museum aims to provide an
interactive way to study the history and spiritual heritage of Kazakhstan. The project is designed to
increase students’ and young people’s interest in national history through modern VR and AR
technologies.
Hypothesis: The use of immersive technologies enables students to better absorb historical
material, increases engagement, and promotes a deeper understanding of cultural heritage compared
to traditional learning methods.
Stages and Procedures of the Research: Collecting and analyzing data on students’ perception of
history; creating a prototype of the virtual museum with 3D models; testing the platform in
educational institutions; gathering feedback and analyzing results.
Research Methodology: Experimental implementation of VR content in the learning process,
observation of participant behavior, surveys to assess interest, and quantitative and qualitative data
analysis.
Novelty and Degree of Independence: This project is the first educational VR museum in
Kazakhstan with national content in the Kazakh language. All development stages, including 3D
modeling, AR card integration, and testing, were carried out independently by the author under the
guidance of a mentor.
Results and Conclusions: Testing showed that 70% of participants demonstrated increased interest
in learning history. The platform proved to be convenient and effective for educational use.
Practical Application: RuhVR can be implemented in schools and other educational institutions
as an interactive supplement to the curriculum, promoting national culture and history among young
people.
