INTRODUCTION
Relevance of the Topic:
In the modern digital era, young people often spend significant time on social media platforms
and digital entertainment, while their interest in national history and culture has been decreasing.
Traditional textbooks and lectures often fail to engage students and do not provide an immersive
experience. Preserving and transmitting national identity is crucial for fostering a sense of
belonging and understanding cultural heritage. Virtual reality (VR) and augmented reality (AR)
technologies provide unique opportunities to make historical education interactive and engaging.
The development of immersive platforms allows students to explore history not only through text
but also through 3D visualization, sound, and interactive storytelling.
Objective of the Work:
The primary goal of this research is to develop RuhVR, the first Kazakh virtual museum, to
introduce national history and cultural heritage to the younger generation in an interactive format.
This platform aims to make history accessible, interesting, and emotionally engaging, enabling
students to experience historical events, artifacts, and traditions in a virtual environment. The
project also seeks to evaluate the effectiveness of VR-based education compared to traditional
learning methods.
Brief Methods for Solving the Tasks:
The work combines several approaches to achieve its objectives:
• Conducting an analytical review of existing VR and AR educational projects globally;
• Developing 3D models of historical artifacts and environments;
• Integrating these models into an interactive VR museum platform with AR-enhanced cards;
• Testing the platform in schools through observational studies and surveys;
• Analyzing user feedback to measure engagement, interest, and educational outcomes.
This approach ensures that the project not only creates a functional virtual museum but also
provides measurable evidence of its educational value, offering an innovative method for
preserving and transmitting Kazakh national heritage.
