I MAIN SECTION
1.1 The Importance of Kazakh Spirituality and History in Educating Generations
Kazakh history and spirituality are central to shaping the identity, values, and worldview of younger
generations. Traditional education often focuses on dates, events, and names, but fails to convey
the cultural and emotional significance of historical events. Integrating spiritual and cultural aspects
into learning helps students understand the roots of their national identity, moral values, and social
responsibilities.
By exploring historical narratives, rituals, literature, and traditions, students develop critical
thinking and cultural literacy. They learn not only facts but also the meaning behind historical
choices, ethical dilemmas, and cultural evolution. Virtual experiences that highlight Kazakh
spirituality—through storytelling, 3D reconstructions of cultural sites, and immersive simulations
of everyday life in past eras—allow students to feel and internalize history rather than just memorize
it.
1.2 Global Experience and the Role of Virtual Museums in Culture
Worldwide, virtual museums and immersive experiences have become powerful tools for education
and cultural preservation. Platforms like Google Expeditions, TimeLooper, and museum VR
applications allow users to explore historical sites, artifacts, and cultural exhibits without leaving
their classrooms. Studies show that immersive VR increases engagement, retention, and motivation
among students compared to traditional textbooks [1][2].
Virtual museums also serve as bridges between generations, connecting contemporary audiences
with historical knowledge in an accessible and interactive way. While global projects provide
valuable experiences, most do not focus on local or minority cultures, leaving a gap in culturally
relevant education. There is a clear opportunity to develop VR platforms that showcase the history
and heritage of specific nations, allowing users to experience their unique culture firsthand.
1.3 Structure and Capabilities of the RuhVR Project
RuhVR is designed as Kazakhstan’s first virtual museum with comprehensive VR and AR
integration. Its main components include:
• Historical Sections: Chronologically organized content from the Stone Age, through the
Kazakh Khanate, Alash Movements, to modern Kazakhstan.
• 3D Artifacts: Accurate models of weapons, clothing, everyday objects, and monuments.
• Immersive Environments: Realistic reconstructions of historical sites, yurts, and battlefields.
