REVIEW
Reviewer: Baurzhan Anesovich Tynyimbaev, 2026
The scientific projects by Amanzhol Bekzhan, Bekzat Khasanov, and Rasul
Mahsot represent a highly significant and relevant initiative in the modern education
sector. Considering the declining interest of young people in history in recent years,
the authors’ idea of teaching Kazakh history through virtual reality (VR) and
augmented reality (AR) technologies is particularly valuable.
The relevance of the project lies in combining traditional education with new
technologies to enhance the quality of learning and present historical heritage from a
fresh perspective. The authors developed an innovative solution based on concrete
historical data, demonstrating both academic rigor and creativity.
The project employs modern approaches such as 3D modeling of historical periods,
displaying cultural artifacts through AR cards, and immersive VR experiences
that allow users to enter historical environments. This approach enables students to
perceive history not only as a theoretical subject but also as an engaging and practical
experience.
The uniqueness of this scientific work is its integration of theory and practice. The
project is ready for effective implementation in education and can be widely applied
in schools, universities, and museums.
Overall, the scientific projects by Amanzhol Bekzhan, Bekzat Khasanov, and
Rasul Mahsot deserve the highest evaluation for their scientific rigor, practical
significance, and innovative content.
